--- body ---
## Context
Companion figure for the HET paper "Un theoreme, sept costumes" / "One
Theorem, Seven Guises", which lives in the sibling project
`polycentric_activity` (tracker `tickets/0011`, manuscript drafted on branch
`t0014-het-manuscrit-v1`, not yet merged). The paper's thesis is that seven
independent literatures (+ a Leontief coda) proved the same network-potentials
theorem without citing each other. This figure makes that claim visually
checkable: a citation-overlap scatter (Y = year, X = PCA1 of a title+abstract
+keywords embedding) showing whether the seven costumes' reference networks
occupy separate regions or overlap.

Author asked to reuse this project's existing OpenAlex/embeddings machinery
rather than duplicate it in `polycentric_activity` (decision: 2026-07-07).

## Relevant files
- `data/het/seeds.csv` -- 71 works cited in the HET manuscript (extracted from
  its `\cite` keys against `polycentric_activity`'s refs.bib + het-refs.bib on
  branch t0014). 18 of the 71 are tagged into 8 "costume" branches.
- `scripts/het_build_corpus.py` -- hop-0/1/2 OpenAlex crawl (seeds -> their
  references -> references of the branch-reachable references). Writes
  `data/het/works.csv` + `data/het/citations.csv`.
- `scripts/het_embed.py` -- BAAI/bge-m3 embeddings (same model/text convention
  as `enrich_embeddings.py`, but standalone: that script's periodization
  filter is 1990-2024 and would drop this 1916-1992 corpus). Writes
  `data/het/embeddings.npz` + `data/het/works_pca.csv` (adds a PCA1 column).
- `scripts/het_plot_overlap.py` -- the figure itself.
- `tests/test_het_build_corpus.py` -- unit tests for the crawl logic.

## Actions
1. Run `uv run python scripts/het_build_corpus.py` (crawl; ~1 min with an
   OpenAlex API key configured).
2. Run `uv run --extra cpu python scripts/het_embed.py` (needs
   `uv sync --group corpus --extra cpu` first).
3. Run `uv run python scripts/het_plot_overlap.py`.
4. Copy `data/het/het_overlap.svg` (+ .png) into `polycentric_activity`,
   natural location `conception/het-overlap-citations.svg`, referenced from
   the manuscript or from a note alongside `conception/het-squelette.md`.

## Verification
- [ ] Seed resolution rate logged and reasonable (64/71 achieved 2026-07-07;
      unresolved are pre-1960s items OpenAlex doesn't index -- Heckscher 1916
      Swedish, Mises 1920 German, two 1951 Cowles book chapters -- documented,
      not silently dropped).
- [ ] `_n_branches > 2` warning does not fire silently (script logs a count if
      it does; current corpus has a max of 2).
- [ ] Figure legend covers all 8 branches + context; overlap wedges visible.

## Invariants
- Does not touch `enrich_embeddings.py`'s shared cache or the main
  `data/catalogs/` corpus (Phase 1/2 contract) -- reads/writes only under
  `data/het/`.
- Only `data/het/seeds.csv` (the curated 71-work bibliography) is committed --
  matches this project's own convention (`content/figures/*` gitignored,
  Phase-1 catalogs DVC-managed): `works.csv`, `works_pca.csv`,
  `citations.csv`, `embeddings.npz`, `het_overlap.{png,svg}` and `pool/` are
  all regenerable from seeds.csv via the three `het_*.py` scripts (see
  Actions) and exceed the repo's 500KB plain-git file limit anyway.

## Exit criteria
- [ ] Figure produced and copied into `polycentric_activity`.
- [ ] `make check-fast` (ruff + unit tests) passes.
